facts.fact_text: Employment in Canada fell 0.1% (-25,000) in January 2025.

facts.fact_text: The employment rate edged down 0.1 percentage point to 60.8%.

evidences.evidence_text: The employment rate edged down 0.1 percentage point to 60.8%.

facts.fact_text: Job losses were concentrated among core-aged women (25–54), down 27,000 (-0.4%).

facts.fact_text: Employment declined in manufacturing (-28,000; -1.5%), educational services (-24,000; -1.5%) and public administration (-10,000; -0.8%).

evidences.evidence_text: By sector, employment declined in manufacturing (-28,000; -1.5%), educational services (-24,000; -1.5%) and public administration (-10,000; -0.8%).

facts.fact_text: Offsetting gains were seen in information, culture and recreation (+17,000; +2.0%), business, building and other support services (+14,000; +2.1%), agriculture (+11,000; +4.5%) and utilities (+4,200; +2.5%).

facts.fact_text: Employment fell sharply in Ontario (-67,000; -0.8%), while Alberta (+20,000; +0.8%), Saskatchewan (+6,100; +1.0%) and Newfoundland and Labrador (+3,800; +1.6%) posted gains.
